1
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:11,800
<i> Bobby!</i>

2
00:00:11,933 --> 00:00:13,133
<i>I just came to pick up
your granddaughter, Sir.</i>

3
00:00:13,267 --> 00:00:14,600
<i>Why, Sir?
Where are we going?</i>

4
00:00:14,733 --> 00:00:16,067
<i> We're going to talk to Daga.</i>

5
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:17,933
<i> No, no, you can't do this.</i>

6
00:00:18,067 --> 00:00:19,200
<i> We had a deal.</i>

7
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:20,900
<i> Boss , we never talked about</i>

8
00:00:21,033 --> 00:00:23,067
<i> this kind of expose.</i>

9
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:25,800
<i>Don't tell me
you're endorsing Joaquin?</i>

10
00:00:25,933 --> 00:00:26,800
<i> That's right.</i>

11
00:00:26,933 --> 00:00:28,767
<i>I'm ready to sacrifice
my campaign</i>

12
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:30,800
<i>just to get rid of all the
crimes</i>

13
00:00:30,933 --> 00:00:31,833
<i> here in Calabari.</i>

14
00:00:31,967 --> 00:00:33,133
<i> We just wanted to ask</i>

15
00:00:33,267 --> 00:00:35,233
<i>if you know someone named
Brando Salazar.</i>

16
00:00:36,633 --> 00:00:37,933
<i> He's known as Daga.</i>

17
00:00:38,067 --> 00:00:39,767
<i>All right then, Daga,
let's go to the precinct.</i>

18
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:41,433
<i> Boss, chill.</i>

19
00:00:41,567 --> 00:00:43,533
<i> I don't trust cops.</i>

20
00:00:43,667 --> 00:00:45,467
<i>How do I know if the boss
planted someone in your group?</i>

21
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:48,433
<i>What if I just call someone
over to sketch him?</i>

22
00:00:48,567 --> 00:00:50,500
<i>You describe the guy to me,
and I'll take care of the rest.</i>

23
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:51,900
<i>You're good.
This is it.</i>

24
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:53,267
<i> This is Boss 's driver.</i>

25
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:54,733
<i>Let's just meet
at the station later.</i>

26
00:00:54,867 --> 00:00:56,300
<i>I have something important
to deal with.</i>

27
00:00:56,433 --> 00:00:58,100
<i>- What about the sketch?
- I'll handle it.</i>

28
00:00:58,233 --> 00:00:59,533
<i> Is this about Daga?</i>

29
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:00,900
<i> Just make sure</i>

30
00:01:01,033 --> 00:01:03,000
<i>every answer you give
to my questions is the truth.</i>

31
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:04,267
<i>If not, we're going
to have a problem.</i>

32
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:06,467
<i>I will have my own
fingers cut off...</i>

33
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:08,900
<i> if you find out I'm lying.</i>

34
00:01:15,733 --> 00:01:18,933
Chief, we already got the sketch

35
00:01:19,067 --> 00:01:22,867
from Daga that shows the man
connected to Boss.

36
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:24,367
Where is the sketch?

37
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:25,633
That's the thing, Sir.

38
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:27,967
Lieutenant Conde said

39
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:29,800
he'd personally deliver it.

40
00:01:30,533 --> 00:01:32,267
He told me
to go ahead here earlier,

41
00:01:32,833 --> 00:01:33,967
but he still hasn't shown up.

42
00:01:35,867 --> 00:01:36,700
Now?

43
00:01:37,433 --> 00:01:40,000
Okay, let's just wait
for him here.

44
00:01:41,433 --> 00:01:42,200
That's it, Sir?

45
00:01:43,067 --> 00:01:44,133
Aren't you wondering

46
00:01:44,267 --> 00:01:46,900
why Lieutenant Conde hasn't
arrived yet?

47
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,233
Why, Enriquez?

48
00:01:48,967 --> 00:01:50,000
What are you trying to say?

49
00:01:55,067 --> 00:01:57,533
Sir, Dr. Cecilia is here.

50
00:01:58,467 --> 00:01:59,467
Let her in.

51
00:02:10,833 --> 00:02:11,600
Oh, Doc.

52
00:02:12,667 --> 00:02:14,100
- Here's the report.
- Oh.

53
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:17,100
Doc!

54
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:19,600
How are you?

55
00:02:19,733 --> 00:02:21,367
High five!

56
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:23,067
How are you?

57
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:25,267
You, Doc, you have not been
replying to me.

58
00:02:25,767 --> 00:02:27,833
Any news?

59
00:02:27,967 --> 00:02:29,300
I'm sorry...

60
00:02:29,867 --> 00:02:31,167
I just got a bit busy.

61
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:33,367
Oh, is that so?

62
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:34,900
Oh, Doc...

63
00:02:35,867 --> 00:02:38,167
What's the result of the
ballistics?

64
00:02:38,667 --> 00:02:39,567
Yes, we have the result.

65
00:02:40,233 --> 00:02:42,733
Based on the ballistic test,

66
00:02:42,867 --> 00:02:45,633
the bullet in Bullet's head is
about 10 years old.

67
00:02:45,933 --> 00:02:47,400
According to our database,

68
00:02:47,567 --> 00:02:48,967
the bullet came from a gun

69
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:52,700
registered to Victor Santiago.

70
00:02:53,433 --> 00:02:54,067
What?

71
00:03:30,333 --> 00:03:31,533
Thank you, Doc.

72
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:40,400
Garcia, text Conde.

73
00:03:41,333 --> 00:03:42,567
Tell him to go here.

74
00:03:54,467 --> 00:03:56,300
Oh, Roman, how's it going?

75
00:03:56,433 --> 00:03:57,400
Everything is good, Boss.

76
00:03:57,533 --> 00:03:58,833
What's our status?

77
00:03:58,967 --> 00:04:00,900
Joaquin keeps attacking us.

78
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,533
Maybe it's time we take action.

79
00:04:03,667 --> 00:04:04,633
Just say the word, Boss.

80
00:04:04,767 --> 00:04:06,000
What do I need to do?

81
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:08,067
I have been itching
to make a move.

82
00:04:11,433 --> 00:04:13,267
- Sir, we'll go ahead.
- All right.

83
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,167
Be safe.

84
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:18,100
Oh, Bok.

85
00:04:18,233 --> 00:04:18,867
Brad.

86
00:04:20,967 --> 00:04:21,633
Sir.

87
00:04:22,067 --> 00:04:23,133
Sit down.

88
00:04:24,667 --> 00:04:25,700
Enriquez said,

89
00:04:26,033 --> 00:04:28,600
you have the sketch
of Boss's guy.

90
00:04:28,767 --> 00:04:29,433
Where is it?

91
00:04:30,167 --> 00:04:31,567
Oh no!

92
00:04:31,933 --> 00:04:33,167
I forgot, Sir.

93
00:04:33,467 --> 00:04:34,300
I left it at home.

94
00:04:34,433 --> 00:04:35,833
I passed by there earlier.

95
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:37,200
You left it, Sir?

96
00:04:38,567 --> 00:04:40,500
Then I should've just
taken it myself.

97
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:44,400
My bad, Enriquez.
I'm only human.

98
00:04:44,533 --> 00:04:45,467
Don't worry, Chief,

99
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:47,300
I'll bring the sketch later.

100
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:48,833
After we are done here,

101
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:51,733
go home and bring me the sketch.

102
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:57,900
We need to know if this guy,

103
00:04:58,033 --> 00:05:00,933
is connected to our cases we are
investigating.

104
00:05:01,533 --> 00:05:03,067
Conde, did you get my message

105
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:05,733
about Dr. Cecilia's report?

106
00:05:07,033 --> 00:05:07,533
Yes, Sir.

107
00:05:08,067 --> 00:05:09,033
What do you think?

108
00:05:10,767 --> 00:05:13,267
The gun is registered
to Victor Santiago,

109
00:05:14,433 --> 00:05:15,667
but is that enough evidence,

110
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,767
to prove he shot Bullet?

111
00:05:18,133 --> 00:05:19,600
That was ten years ago.

112
00:05:19,833 --> 00:05:21,000
If it wasn't him,

113
00:05:21,133 --> 00:05:23,033
what a crazy coincidence.

114
00:05:23,167 --> 00:05:25,667
Let's start with the bank
robbery mask,

115
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:28,067
then the poison used on Sonny,

116
00:05:28,367 --> 00:05:30,667
and now this bullet
in Bullet's head.

117
00:05:31,367 --> 00:05:35,367
You're jumping to conclusions,
Enriquez.

118
00:05:36,433 --> 00:05:39,767
Sure, those are a lot of
coincidences,

119
00:05:40,167 --> 00:05:44,200
but in court, evidence weighs
more than coincidence.

120
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:45,700
Even if we prove,

121
00:05:45,833 --> 00:05:48,467
that Victor Santiago
shot Bullet,

122
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:51,000
that doesn't prove
he masterminded...

123
00:05:51,133 --> 00:05:52,433
the museum heist,

124
00:05:52,567 --> 00:05:54,200
or the San Isidro bank robbery.

125
00:05:54,333 --> 00:05:55,933
There's still a long way to go.

126
00:05:56,067 --> 00:05:57,700
But isn't this enough

127
00:05:57,833 --> 00:06:00,400
to start a formal investigation?

128
00:06:00,967 --> 00:06:01,767
That's enough.

129
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,633
I don't want this affecting
the election.

130
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:13,600
I don't want to owe any
politician anything.

131
00:06:14,033 --> 00:06:14,733
Wait, Sir.

132
00:06:15,267 --> 00:06:17,367
Are you saying we should hold
off the investigation?

133
00:06:17,733 --> 00:06:18,833
Not exactly, Enriquez.

134
00:06:20,667 --> 00:06:27,267
We have a responsibility to the
people and to ourselves.

135
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:29,667
So, we will continue
the investigation.

136
00:06:31,467 --> 00:06:32,933
But as much as possible,

137
00:06:33,367 --> 00:06:35,033
we can't let the public know

138
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:39,633
that Victor Santiago
is under investigation.

139
00:06:41,533 --> 00:06:43,367
- Is that clear?
- Yes, Sir.

140
00:06:46,100 --> 00:06:48,700
All right, I still have
things to handle.

141
00:06:49,733 --> 00:06:50,367
Dismissed.

142
00:07:02,733 --> 00:07:03,967
I'll go ahead, Enriquez.

143
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:07,600
Where were you earlier, Sir?

144
00:07:13,367 --> 00:07:14,633
Why should I tell you?

145
00:07:15,933 --> 00:07:16,867
Are you my mother?

146
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,900
I offered to bring
the sketch here,

147
00:07:20,467 --> 00:07:21,667
but you declined.

148
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:23,500
You said you'd do it yourself,
remember?

149
00:07:24,433 --> 00:07:25,933
That's why I'm asking now!

150
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:28,000
This is useless, Enriquez.

151
00:07:29,133 --> 00:07:32,400
No matter what I do,
you'll just suspect me.

152
00:07:32,767 --> 00:07:33,467
Why, Sir?

153
00:07:34,433 --> 00:07:35,533
Can you really blame me?

154
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:56,033
Bro, we still need
to retrieve that.

155
00:07:56,167 --> 00:07:58,333
- Forward to, Bobby.
- Captain! Captain!

156
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:02,867
- What's this commotion?
- Captain, look!

157
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,700
He's owed us money for so long!

158
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:06,833
He owes me five hundred pesos,
Captain.

159
00:08:06,967 --> 00:08:08,000
He owes me one thousand five
hundred pesos.

160
00:08:08,133 --> 00:08:09,633
Mine's just a small amount,
just two thousand pesos.

161
00:08:09,767 --> 00:08:11,967
- Four thousand pesos?
- Yes, Captain.

162
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:14,433
What did you do with the money
you borrowed from all of them?

163
00:08:14,567 --> 00:08:16,367
I'll pay them back, Captain.

164
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:17,767
It's just that I haven't been
lucky yet.

165
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:19,400
- Lucky?
- You know, Captain...

166
00:08:19,533 --> 00:08:20,667
he's addicted to "scatter."

167
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,767
Scatter? What is that?

168
00:08:22,933 --> 00:08:24,167
It's online gambling, Captain.

169
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:25,533
- Yes.
- He's lucky...

170
00:08:25,667 --> 00:08:26,833
we haven't beaten him up yet.

171
00:08:26,967 --> 00:08:28,000
We're this close
to going after him.

172
00:08:28,133 --> 00:08:30,933
Gambling? You gambled
all their money?

173
00:08:31,067 --> 00:08:32,733
I was just trying my luck,
Captain!

174
00:08:35,167 --> 00:08:37,233
You scumbag!

175
00:08:39,967 --> 00:08:41,733
Why? Why?

176
00:08:41,867 --> 00:08:43,133
What are you fighting over?

177
00:08:43,267 --> 00:08:45,600
This guy, he spent all our money
in gambling!

178
00:08:45,733 --> 00:08:46,800
Oh!

179
00:08:46,933 --> 00:08:48,667
Electric bill payment,

180
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,433
rent payment,

181
00:08:50,567 --> 00:08:53,167
even my money
for sanitary napkin!

182
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:54,600
Let's beat him up, Captain!

183
00:08:54,767 --> 00:08:56,533
You're unbelievable!

184
00:08:56,667 --> 00:08:59,067
Okay, Melba, Melba,
let it go, just let it go.

185
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:02,900
I'll talk to your landlady
about the rent.

186
00:09:03,033 --> 00:09:04,533
If you need electricity,

187
00:09:04,667 --> 00:09:06,700
come charge your phones
at the village hall.

188
00:09:06,833 --> 00:09:08,800
You can charge your phones here.

189
00:09:08,933 --> 00:09:10,433
But what about the money
that Owa owes us?

190
00:09:10,567 --> 00:09:11,700
Don't worry.

191
00:09:11,833 --> 00:09:13,500
Owa will pay you back.

192
00:09:13,633 --> 00:09:14,767
How, Captain?

193
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:16,000
- He doesn't even have a job!
- That's right.

194
00:09:16,133 --> 00:09:17,633
How is he going to pay us
back then, Captain?

195
00:09:17,767 --> 00:09:18,833
If that is the case.

196
00:09:18,967 --> 00:09:21,333
-That's not acceptable.
-I'll make him a village patrol!

197
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:28,200
And you, Owa,
you need to straighten up.

198
00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:30,067
If you gamble again,

199
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:34,467
I'll let your wife and all these
people beat you.

200
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:36,633
Yes, I promise no more gambling.

201
00:09:36,767 --> 00:09:38,467
I'm fine being beaten
by my wife,

202
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,600
just not these ugly people!

203
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:42,133
Melba, my love...

204
00:09:42,267 --> 00:09:43,367
- I'm sorry, please forgive me.
- Cut it out.

205
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:46,567
That's why you all need to stop
that scatter thing, okay?

206
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:49,767
It won't do you any good.

207
00:09:49,900 --> 00:09:51,200
Yes, Ma'am.

208
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:52,500
Oh, Melba...

209
00:09:54,967 --> 00:09:56,800
Noble, I need you to look
something up.

210
00:09:56,933 --> 00:09:57,600
What is it, Ma'am?

211
00:09:59,133 --> 00:10:00,900
I need a police report

212
00:10:01,067 --> 00:10:02,433
from ten years ago.

213
00:10:02,567 --> 00:10:04,167
Check the file from...

214
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:04,867
Oh.

215
00:10:07,067 --> 00:10:07,833
What is this, Sir?

216
00:10:08,667 --> 00:10:09,967
Police report
from ten years ago.

217
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:12,600
It says Victor Santiago's gun
was reported stolen.

218
00:10:13,167 --> 00:10:14,900
Then whoever stole that gun,

219
00:10:15,033 --> 00:10:17,067
could've been the one
who shot Bullet.

220
00:10:17,467 --> 00:10:18,800
But we don't know
the exact date,

221
00:10:18,933 --> 00:10:20,300
when Bullet was shot.

222
00:10:21,533 --> 00:10:24,267
What if it happened
before the theft?

223
00:10:26,567 --> 00:10:27,700
Then that would mean...

224
00:10:28,067 --> 00:10:29,900
Boss might still have something
to do with it.

225
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,267
All right, here is the deal.
Enriquez.

226
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:36,467
If you can prove that Boss
really did the shooting,

227
00:10:37,300 --> 00:10:38,700
I'll personally
arrest him myself.

228
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:48,467
He's drunk.

229
00:10:50,700 --> 00:10:52,100
Wait, sorry, sorry, sorry.

230
00:10:52,233 --> 00:10:53,767
Can your friend
still handle this?

231
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:54,700
She's weak.

232
00:10:54,833 --> 00:10:56,267
What? Such a lightweight.

233
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:58,200
What a lightweight.

234
00:10:58,333 --> 00:10:59,367
Wait, guys, wait.

235
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:00,900
- Hey! Hold on!
- Stay there!

236
00:11:01,033 --> 00:11:01,900
Wait a second!

237
00:11:06,933 --> 00:11:07,767
Reign?

238
00:11:15,733 --> 00:11:17,133
What are you doing here?

239
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,733
Reign, you're drunk.

240
00:11:19,767 --> 00:11:21,267
Let's go, I'll take you home.

241
00:11:22,467 --> 00:11:23,967
I don't need your help.

242
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:25,067
So can you just...

243
00:11:25,633 --> 00:11:26,733
just leave me alone?

244
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:30,300
Your friends already left you.

245
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:32,200
Come on, I'll take you home.

246
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:33,200
- I'll drop you off at...
- What the heck?

247
00:11:33,333 --> 00:11:35,033
I said I don't need your help!

248
00:11:39,267 --> 00:11:40,967
I spoke with Godfather Karlo.

249
00:11:41,567 --> 00:11:44,100
<i>Godfather, I'm sorry again about
what happened to godmother.</i>

250
00:11:45,767 --> 00:11:47,067
<i> I'm also sorry...</i>

251
00:11:48,133 --> 00:11:49,267
<i> I blamed you.</i>

252
00:11:50,567 --> 00:11:52,900
<i> Even if I knew deep down...</i>

253
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:55,133
<i> it wasn't really your fault.</i>

254
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:58,867
<i>Dina was just doing her job
as a police officer.</i>

255
00:11:59,933 --> 00:12:01,800
<i> Since I married Dina,</i>

256
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:03,900
<i>I already knew something like
this could happen.</i>

257
00:12:04,467 --> 00:12:06,467
<i> So even if it hurts,</i>

258
00:12:06,733 --> 00:12:08,033
<i> I accepted it.</i>

259
00:12:08,967 --> 00:12:10,033
<i> But, Reign...</i>

260
00:12:10,467 --> 00:12:12,133
<i> Reign wasn't prepared.</i>

261
00:12:12,367 --> 00:12:14,467
<i>That's why, you know,
she's acting out.</i>

262
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,500
<i> I left my job,</i>

263
00:12:16,933 --> 00:12:19,067
<i>so I could focus on your
god-sibling.</i>

264
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:22,533
<i>At least here,
driving a tricycle,</i>

265
00:12:22,667 --> 00:12:24,033
<i> I manage my own time.</i>

266
00:12:24,467 --> 00:12:27,600
<i> Anytime Reign needs me,</i>

267
00:12:27,733 --> 00:12:29,033
<i> I'm there for her.</i>

268
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:31,667
<i> But it is still different.</i>

269
00:12:32,367 --> 00:12:33,833
<i>It's still different
when Dina's around.</i>

270
00:12:36,267 --> 00:12:39,300
<i> Sometimes, I think...</i>

271
00:12:40,967 --> 00:12:42,433
<i> I wish I was the one who died,</i>

272
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,267
<i> instead of Dina.</i>

273
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:47,900
<i>Maybe Reign would be
doing better.</i>

274
00:12:49,867 --> 00:12:53,300
<i>She'd have her mother,
someone to take care of her.</i>

275
00:12:56,133 --> 00:12:57,000
So what now?

276
00:12:58,533 --> 00:13:00,000
Did he snitch on me to you?

277
00:13:00,567 --> 00:13:01,567
Come on!

278
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:03,633
I'm already 18.

279
00:13:04,167 --> 00:13:06,300
I can do whatever I want.

280
00:13:06,967 --> 00:13:09,200
And do you know what
I want right now?

281
00:13:10,567 --> 00:13:12,467
What I really want right now?

282
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:17,433
I want you out of my sight.

283
00:13:18,633 --> 00:13:20,300
Maybe you forgot...

284
00:13:20,733 --> 00:13:22,667
I lost my mom because of you.

285
00:13:24,067 --> 00:13:26,767
You're a worthless person, okay?

286
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,433
Reign!

287
00:13:35,567 --> 00:13:36,933
I don't need your help!

288
00:13:57,667 --> 00:13:59,267
Dear, come on!

289
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,400
Let's eat!

290
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:07,733
Is my granddaughter dealing with
something?

291
00:14:12,333 --> 00:14:15,467
Grandmother,
I just don't get it.

292
00:14:15,967 --> 00:14:19,400
Sir Tonyo's actions
are so questionable,

293
00:14:19,667 --> 00:14:22,267
But not one of my questions
gets answered.

294
00:14:24,067 --> 00:14:26,167
Didn't he answer you before?

295
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:28,667
The issue with Boss?
That was personal.

296
00:14:28,833 --> 00:14:30,767
It had nothing to do
with your case.

297
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:33,600
Oh my, Grandmother.

298
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:36,900
I just don't believe
in him anymore.

299
00:14:37,367 --> 00:14:38,533
You don't believe in him,

300
00:14:38,667 --> 00:14:41,933
Or are you just choosing not to
believe he's a decent cop?

301
00:14:42,633 --> 00:14:44,633
You had a crush on him,
didn't you?

302
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:47,933
Oh please, Grandmother.
Not anymore.

303
00:14:48,067 --> 00:14:49,100
That's over.

304
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,900
I'm not going to fall
for Sir Tonyo...

305
00:14:52,033 --> 00:14:53,533
bacause he's a liar.

306
00:14:54,067 --> 00:14:56,433
Oh, so because he's a liar...

307
00:14:56,567 --> 00:14:58,567
What's going on with you,
Grandmother?

308
00:14:59,033 --> 00:15:01,567
Maybe you're just finding
faults,

309
00:15:01,967 --> 00:15:04,233
Because you don't want
to fall for him.

310
00:15:06,267 --> 00:15:07,833
Oh please, Grandmother.

311
00:15:07,967 --> 00:15:09,400
Just eat already.

312
00:15:11,733 --> 00:15:13,233
That's delicious!

313
00:15:25,833 --> 00:15:26,533
Boss!

314
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:43,467
How was your meeting
with Victor?

315
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:44,467
It went okay, Boss.

316
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,133
To this day,
he's still clueless.

317
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:48,900
He's convinced
the mayor is behind

318
00:15:49,033 --> 00:15:50,367
everything happening to him.

319
00:15:51,133 --> 00:15:52,533
Now he wants me to look into

320
00:15:52,667 --> 00:15:54,633
this reporter, Mira.

321
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:57,567
He thinks the mayor

322
00:15:58,200 --> 00:16:00,367
is paying her off too.

323
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:04,900
Take care of Daga.

324
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:08,133
Wait, take care of Daga?

325
00:16:09,033 --> 00:16:12,067
Boss, isn't Daga
our only witness

326
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:13,900
against Victor Santiago?

327
00:16:15,133 --> 00:16:16,333
If Daga dies,

328
00:16:17,333 --> 00:16:18,500
it might backfire...

329
00:16:18,633 --> 00:16:19,900
Since when did you start...

330
00:16:20,033 --> 00:16:22,233
questioning my decisions?

331
00:16:23,033 --> 00:16:24,700
If Daga dies,

332
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:27,433
who do you think they'll blame?
Isn't it Victor?

333
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:29,467
- I'm sorry, Boss.
- And after that?

334
00:16:30,967 --> 00:16:33,333
It's guaranteed that
my dad wins the election.

335
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:36,067
Do you understand?

336
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,133
Yes, Boss.

337
00:16:37,867 --> 00:16:39,167
Boss...

338
00:16:45,533 --> 00:16:50,133
Your father owes you big for
winning this election, Boss.

339
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:52,333
He should be thanking you.

340
00:16:54,467 --> 00:16:55,400
Don't worry.

341
00:16:57,667 --> 00:17:01,933
Everyone who owes me,
pays.

342
00:17:02,733 --> 00:17:03,933
Yes, Boss.

343
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:05,800
Where are you taking me?

344
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:08,300
- All right!
- Please, stop!

345
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:09,667
That's enough!

346
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:10,867
Stand up, stand up!

347
00:17:12,433 --> 00:17:14,333
Please have mercy on me!

348
00:17:19,033 --> 00:17:20,967
Boss...

349
00:17:22,033 --> 00:17:24,400
Where's Mr. Salvacion?

350
00:17:24,533 --> 00:17:25,800
I don't know, Boss!

351
00:17:25,933 --> 00:17:28,733
He needs to pay his debt.

352
00:17:28,867 --> 00:17:29,967
You really don't know
where he is?

353
00:17:30,100 --> 00:17:31,600
I really don't!

354
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,100
What I hate the most...

355
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:35,667
Don't kill me, Boss!

356
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,300
is making me look like a fool.

357
00:17:37,433 --> 00:17:39,100
Please, have mercy,
I don't want to die...

358
00:17:45,133 --> 00:17:45,867
All of you...

359
00:17:47,133 --> 00:17:51,367
why can't you find
Mr. Salvacion?

360
00:17:51,533 --> 00:17:53,600
Boss, we're really having a hard
time finding him...

361
00:17:53,733 --> 00:17:54,767
You are having a hard time?

362
00:18:02,167 --> 00:18:03,633
Hey, this still looks usable.

363
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:07,300
Perfect.

364
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:09,033
These are still good.

365
00:18:13,267 --> 00:18:14,500
I wonder what's in here...

366
00:18:15,567 --> 00:18:16,600
Plastic...

367
00:18:18,067 --> 00:18:19,300
One...

368
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:23,600
Hey, there it is! Jackpot!

369
00:18:24,100 --> 00:18:24,967
There's a lot!

370
00:18:25,633 --> 00:18:26,433
Two...

371
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:29,367
There, jackpot...

372
00:18:29,967 --> 00:18:31,400
Oh, Mister...

373
00:18:35,967 --> 00:18:37,200
Boss...

374
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:38,433
Boss...

375
00:18:41,433 --> 00:18:43,200
Dead body!
There's a dead body here!

376
00:18:43,333 --> 00:18:44,600
There's a dead body!

377
00:18:44,733 --> 00:18:47,133
Dead body! Help!

378
00:18:47,267 --> 00:18:49,667
Call the police!
Call the police!

379
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:51,767
Ma'am, let your god-sibling be.

380
00:18:52,367 --> 00:18:53,900
You're doing everything
you can to solve

381
00:18:54,033 --> 00:18:54,800
your godmother's case.

382
00:18:57,833 --> 00:19:00,333
So, what are you consulting us
for, Noble?

383
00:19:00,467 --> 00:19:02,933
Oh, Ma'am, a mother
came to me yesterday.

384
00:19:03,367 --> 00:19:04,233
She said her daughter
was recruited

385
00:19:04,367 --> 00:19:05,533
to go to the Middle East.

386
00:19:05,667 --> 00:19:07,933
- Mmm.
- But since she left,

387
00:19:08,067 --> 00:19:09,033
they haven't been able to
contact her.

388
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:12,267
Then refer her
to Overseas Employment.

389
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:14,733
That's what I told her too,
Ma'am.

390
00:19:14,967 --> 00:19:16,567
But she suspects her daughter
was victimized by a syndicate.

391
00:19:16,933 --> 00:19:18,200
Human trafficking?

392
00:19:18,667 --> 00:19:19,533
That's what I think too, Ma'am.

393
00:19:20,433 --> 00:19:21,367
Enriquez!

394
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:23,433
Let's go, come with me.

395
00:19:23,567 --> 00:19:24,400
Where to, Sir?

396
00:19:24,700 --> 00:19:26,067
Daga's been taken out.

397
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,067
- What?
- Let's go!

398
00:19:29,267 --> 00:19:30,733
Noble, we'll talk later.

399
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,133
Okay, Ma'am.

400
00:19:32,267 --> 00:19:34,333
<i> The body of Brando Salazar,</i>

401
00:19:34,467 --> 00:19:36,167
<i> known as Daga,</i>

402
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:38,400
<i>was found in an alley early
this morning.</i>

403
00:19:38,633 --> 00:19:41,333
<i>Daga is known
to be a whistleblower,</i>

404
00:19:41,467 --> 00:19:43,433
<i> who claimed he was paid,</i>

405
00:19:43,567 --> 00:19:45,933
<i>by mayoral candidate
Victor Santiago,</i>

406
00:19:46,067 --> 00:19:47,867
<i>to incite trouble during
a local basketball league</i>

407
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:49,300
<i> in Barangay Sta. Ana.</i>

408
00:19:49,967 --> 00:19:53,000
Mommy, could Uncle Victor
really do that?

409
00:19:53,267 --> 00:19:55,200
I honestly don't know anymore,
Dear.

410
00:19:55,667 --> 00:19:58,267
I can't believe Victor would be
capable of something like that.

411
00:19:58,567 --> 00:20:01,067
Yes, my dear, even
I can't believe it.

412
00:20:02,033 --> 00:20:04,867
Sure, Victor benefits from
Daga's death,

413
00:20:06,033 --> 00:20:09,267
but that doesn't mean
he's behind it.

414
00:20:11,367 --> 00:20:13,667
This is really my regular route
in the morning,

415
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:16,700
then I just saw the body there.

416
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:19,867
You didn't see anyone else
around?

417
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,133
No, Ma'am.

418
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:23,233
It was still really early.

419
00:20:26,033 --> 00:20:26,933
All right.

420
00:20:27,067 --> 00:20:29,333
We'll contact you if we have
more questions.

421
00:20:29,467 --> 00:20:30,600
Okay, Sir, Ma'am.

422
00:20:30,933 --> 00:20:31,667
Okay.

423
00:20:32,700 --> 00:20:33,900
So what's the situation here?

424
00:20:35,367 --> 00:20:37,533
- Enriquez, Garcia.
- Sir.

425
00:20:38,167 --> 00:20:39,067
Any findings?

426
00:20:39,933 --> 00:20:41,000
Still nothing, Chief.

427
00:20:41,467 --> 00:20:42,900
No strong leads so far.

428
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:46,133
Enriquez, what are you thinking?

429
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:48,667
Sir, isn't this too much
of a coincidence?

430
00:20:49,133 --> 00:20:50,700
- Right after...
- Enriquez.

431
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:52,867
Let's figure out
who did this first.

432
00:20:55,133 --> 00:20:55,733
All right?

433
00:20:56,633 --> 00:20:58,400
Keep me posted if there are
any developments.

434
00:20:58,533 --> 00:20:59,600
I'll be in the car.

435
00:21:00,267 --> 00:21:01,633
- Yes, Sir.
- Yes, Sir.

436
00:21:01,767 --> 00:21:02,533
Okay.

437
00:21:03,867 --> 00:21:04,867
Oh, excuse me.

438
00:21:08,933 --> 00:21:11,433
Enriquez, you're so stubborn.

439
00:21:11,900 --> 00:21:13,467
I told you to focus on the lead
for now.

440
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:15,867
Forget the doubts
and so-called coincidences.

441
00:21:19,733 --> 00:21:21,433
Where's Lieutenant Conde?

442
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:26,800
I tried calling him,
but he's not answering.

443
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,967
But don't worry.
I've got a new lead now.

444
00:21:32,133 --> 00:21:33,000
Gang war.

445
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:35,300
That's why we're gpimg
somewhere.

446
00:21:43,467 --> 00:21:44,400
Boss! Boss!

447
00:21:44,533 --> 00:21:46,000
We just have a few questions.

448
00:21:46,133 --> 00:21:47,167
Can you answer them, please?

449
00:21:47,300 --> 00:21:49,367
What can you say
about Daga's death?

450
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:50,633
I know you're thinking

451
00:21:50,767 --> 00:21:52,867
I had something to do with what
happened to Daga

452
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:55,833
because of those exposés
he did on me.

453
00:21:56,333 --> 00:21:57,667
But here's the big picture...

454
00:21:58,233 --> 00:22:00,967
Brando Salazar smeared my name,

455
00:22:01,467 --> 00:22:03,800
so I sued him for libel....

456
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:06,867
That was the only way...

457
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:08,300
I could prove to everyone,

458
00:22:08,433 --> 00:22:12,300
that this was a demolition job
against me.

459
00:22:13,833 --> 00:22:15,867
Just follow my lead, Enriquez.

460
00:22:16,033 --> 00:22:17,067
Watch and learn.

461
00:22:17,633 --> 00:22:21,967
We just need to find the leader
of Daga's rival group.

462
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:23,900
Sir, you really think
it was them?

463
00:22:24,767 --> 00:22:26,300
What would their motive be?

464
00:22:27,733 --> 00:22:29,100
Do they want to get their
revenge from Daga?

465
00:22:29,833 --> 00:22:31,300
That's what we need to find out.

466
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:36,067
- How much?
- Miss...

467
00:22:36,867 --> 00:22:38,100
How much for the turon?

468
00:22:38,567 --> 00:22:39,133
Sir...

469
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:41,800
Isn't that him?

470
00:22:45,633 --> 00:22:46,567
Hey!

471
00:22:54,300 --> 00:22:56,300
Hey, Stop right there!

472
00:22:59,267 --> 00:23:00,467
You jerk, you made us
run after you.

473
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:01,767
Don't hurt me!

474
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:03,100
I'm tone-deaf!

475
00:23:03,233 --> 00:23:04,433
What are you talking about?

476
00:23:04,567 --> 00:23:06,400
Didn't you guys kill Daga?

477
00:23:06,533 --> 00:23:08,000
I'm sure that I'm your next
target.

478
00:23:08,133 --> 00:23:09,833
Why do you think you're next?

479
00:23:09,967 --> 00:23:11,667
Do you know who killed Daga?

480
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:13,300
Aren't you the leader
of San Martin?

481
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,700
- Yes!
- What do you know about Daga

482
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:16,933
and his exposé?

483
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:20,900
You ask a lot of questions.

484
00:23:21,033 --> 00:23:22,467
You're gonna need to grease
the wheels.

485
00:23:22,633 --> 00:23:24,700
Oh, bribe, right?
All right then.

486
00:23:24,833 --> 00:23:25,967
Come with us to the precinct.

487
00:23:26,100 --> 00:23:27,000
We've got a slide there...

488
00:23:27,133 --> 00:23:28,200
you can grease it all you want.
Let's go.

489
00:23:28,333 --> 00:23:30,067
No, no, no.

490
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:32,467
Okay, I'll talk now.

491
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:34,433
- What?
- You know, Daga...

492
00:23:35,233 --> 00:23:36,933
our gang knows him.

493
00:23:37,467 --> 00:23:39,400
We weren't even rivals with him.

494
00:23:39,733 --> 00:23:42,633
So the riot in league is just
for show,

495
00:23:42,767 --> 00:23:44,067
jusr like what Daga said?

496
00:23:44,433 --> 00:23:45,867
We'll ask you again.

497
00:23:46,267 --> 00:23:48,833
What do you have to do with
Daga's death?

498
00:23:49,333 --> 00:23:51,800
Of course, there are talks on
the streets

499
00:23:52,033 --> 00:23:53,300
that Boss had him killed

500
00:23:53,433 --> 00:23:55,067
But there's no proof on that.

501
00:23:55,667 --> 00:23:56,867
If you want,

502
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:59,200
just talk
to Daga's gang directly.

503
00:23:59,333 --> 00:24:01,500
They probably know more
than we do.

504
00:24:08,533 --> 00:24:10,567
Sir, have you contacted Sir
Tonyo?

505
00:24:11,300 --> 00:24:12,700
Not yet.

506
00:24:13,267 --> 00:24:15,567
Maybe he's just taking care of
something.

507
00:24:16,267 --> 00:24:18,800
Oh, taking care of something...

508
00:24:19,767 --> 00:24:22,667
Enriquez, don't go poking around
again, all right?

509
00:24:24,333 --> 00:24:27,800
Sir, did you know that Sir Tonyo
already admitted to me

510
00:24:27,933 --> 00:24:29,600
that Boss is his father?

511
00:24:30,967 --> 00:24:32,500
So what?

512
00:24:33,267 --> 00:24:34,700
You've known for a long time,
haven't you, Sir?

513
00:24:36,033 --> 00:24:37,033
You know...

514
00:24:38,800 --> 00:24:40,367
Tonyo and I are batchmates.

515
00:24:40,500 --> 00:24:42,100
It's no secret to us anymore.

516
00:24:43,433 --> 00:24:44,467
Enriquez...

517
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:47,367
Tonyo's a good cop.

518
00:24:48,167 --> 00:24:51,467
His relationship with Boss has
nothing to do

519
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:53,567
with the cases we're handling.

520
00:25:12,700 --> 00:25:14,200
Our condolences.

521
00:25:20,833 --> 00:25:21,600
Thank you.

522
00:25:23,533 --> 00:25:26,000
We're here to help you

523
00:25:26,133 --> 00:25:28,300
find out who killed Daga.

524
00:25:30,033 --> 00:25:31,033
We also want to know

525
00:25:31,167 --> 00:25:33,600
if you have any other
information

526
00:25:33,967 --> 00:25:35,967
that could help
our investigation.

527
00:25:40,133 --> 00:25:45,233
Do you know who
Daga last spoke to,

528
00:25:46,100 --> 00:25:48,033
or anyone suspicious?

529
00:25:48,733 --> 00:25:49,300
There is.

530
00:25:53,300 --> 00:25:54,500
I was walking that night

531
00:25:54,633 --> 00:25:57,133
when I heard Daga talking
to someone at the corner.

532
00:25:58,433 --> 00:25:59,533
<i> What do you want?</i>

533
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:02,767
<i> I trusted you cops.</i>

534
00:26:11,267 --> 00:26:14,133
When I got there, he was gone.

535
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:17,033
Someone had taken Daga.

536
00:26:21,233 --> 00:26:23,433
Do you have any idea who it was?

537
00:26:23,867 --> 00:26:24,600
None.

538
00:26:26,100 --> 00:26:27,600
He didn't mention any names.

539
00:26:29,200 --> 00:26:33,533
But I heard it clearly, straight
from Daga's mouth,

540
00:26:34,433 --> 00:26:36,500
that was talking to a cop.

541
00:26:38,733 --> 00:26:41,133
A cop he trusted.

542
00:26:44,667 --> 00:26:47,133
We're here to help with the
investigation.

543
00:26:48,700 --> 00:26:49,567
We'll sort this out.

544
00:26:49,700 --> 00:26:52,167
We'll find out who killed Daga.

545
00:26:53,300 --> 00:26:55,533
Trust me, Buddy.

546
00:27:03,133 --> 00:27:04,733
I am not your buddy.

547
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:13,500
A cop killed one of our own.

548
00:27:15,833 --> 00:27:17,333
And we're not...

549
00:27:17,900 --> 00:27:19,867
going to let this go
without payback!

550
00:27:20,600 --> 00:27:21,533
What?

551
00:27:21,900 --> 00:27:23,600
Hey, neighbors!

552
00:27:26,433 --> 00:27:28,367
You'll all pay for this!

553
00:27:35,733 --> 00:27:36,833
Lieutenant Charlie Samson,

554
00:27:36,967 --> 00:27:38,233
welcome to Station 12.

555
00:27:38,567 --> 00:27:40,733
They're here because
they need our help

556
00:27:40,867 --> 00:27:42,000
with their case.

557
00:27:42,133 --> 00:27:43,367
- Charlie?
- Bobby.

558
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:45,200
You may not be a bad person,

559
00:27:45,333 --> 00:27:47,400
but you were still a bad father.

560
00:27:47,533 --> 00:27:48,800
But I want to make up for it.

561
00:27:48,967 --> 00:27:50,333
Give me a job.

562
00:27:50,467 --> 00:27:51,533
Make me your bodyguard.

563
00:27:51,667 --> 00:27:53,233
You really are an actor, Boss!

564
00:27:53,367 --> 00:27:54,967
You're so good at pretending!

565
00:27:55,100 --> 00:27:56,067
You're unbelievable, Bobby!

566
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:57,333
You should feel guilty!

567
00:27:57,467 --> 00:27:58,867
Who knows what's happening
to him now?

568
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:00,700
It's exciting here
in Calabari, right?

569
00:28:00,833 --> 00:28:02,433
Maybe I should transfer
to Station 12.

570
00:28:02,567 --> 00:28:03,533
Seriously?

571
00:28:03,667 --> 00:28:05,167
I want to be close again with
Sergeant Enriquez.

572
00:28:05,300 --> 00:28:06,800
Lieutenant Conde...
